SPI Packet/buffer interface for sending data over an SPI bus. This interface provides a split-phase send command which can be used for sending, receiving or both. It is a "send" command because reading from the SPI requires writing bytes. The send call allows NULL parameters for receive or send only operations. This interface is for buffer based transfers where the microcontroller is the master (clocking) device.
Often, an SPI bus must first be acquired using a Resource interface before sending commands with SPIPacket. In the case of multiple devices attached to a single SPI bus, chip select pins are often also used.
@author Philip Levis @author Jonathan Hui @author Joe Polastre Revision: $Revision: 1.1.2.1 $

Send a message over the SPI bus.

@param txBuf A pointer to the buffer to send over the bus. If this
             parameter is NULL, then the SPI will send zeroes.
@param rxBuf A pointer to the buffer where received data should
             be stored. If this parameter is NULL, then the SPI will
             discard incoming bytes.
@param len   Length of the message.  Note that non-NULL rxBuf and txBuf
             parameters must be AT LEAST as large as len, or the SPI
             will overflow a buffer.

@return SUCCESS if the request was accepted for transfer

